      "review_summary": "The PR changes session-origin merging so internal or non-delivery turns preserve a bound channel identity while real deliverable channel switches still clear stale channel-keyed origin fields.\n\nPR surface: Source +10, Tests +42. Total +52 across 2 files.\n\nReproducibility: yes. Source inspection and the PR's redacted runtime output show current main erases the four bound origin fields after a non-delivery webchat turn, and the same helper is the durable metadata merge boundary.",
